about.summary: It is a dedicated package to WELL pseudo random generators, which were introduced in Panneton et al. (2006), ``Improved Long-Period Generators Based on Linear Recurrences Modulo 2'', ACM Transactions on Mathematical Software. But this package is not intended to be used directly, you are strongly __encouraged__ to use the 'randtoolbox' package, which depends on this package.

name: r-rngwell
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.10-6' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rngwell
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/rngWELL_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/rngWELL/rngWELL_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7b0b695f467c8b58cd8406d5554cb5fc62ab14689c89052b70f5487c9366525e

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}grep              # [win]
    - {{ posix }}autoconf
    - {{ posix }}automake          # [not win]
    - {{ posix }}automake-wrapper  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}pkg-config
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('rngWELL')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('rngWELL')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=rngWELL
  license: BSD_3_clause
  summary: It is a dedicated package to WELL pseudo random generators, which were introduced
    in Panneton et al. (2006), ``Improved Long-Period Generators Based on Linear Recurrences
    Modulo 2'', ACM Transactions on Mathematical Software. But this package is not intended
    to be used directly, you are strongly __encouraged__ to use the 'randtoolbox' package,
    which depends on this package.
  license_family: BSD
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/BSD_3_clause'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

But this package is not intended to be used directly, you are strongly __encouraged__ to use the 'randtoolbox' package, which depends on this package.
